{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place berries and sugar into mixing bowl and purée <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer approximately 8 oz of puréed berries to a bowl and set aside.","Add gelatin, sprinkling around outside edges avoiding blades and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 2<b>, until completely dissolved. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and heat <b>2 min\/140°F\/speed 1<b>.","Add water and heat <b>2 min\/140°F\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add reserved puréed berries and ricotta and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer mixture into a large bowl and refrigerate until gelatin starts to set and mixture has the consistency of heavy cream (approx. 30 min). Clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and without setting a time whip <strong>speed 3<\/strong>, until desired stiffness is achieved, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Gently fold whipped cream into fruit mixture with spatula.","Divide fruit mousse into dessert bowls and refrigerate for 4 hours.","Garnish with berries and fresh mint leaves and serve chilled."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["11 oz fresh mixed red berries (e.g. strawberries, raspberries), plus extra to garnish","7 oz sugar","1 tbsp unflavored gelatin powder","2 oz water","9 oz ricotta cheese","9 oz heavy whipping cream,","fresh mint leaves, to garnish"]}],"id":"r91236","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-j7IogTcHrYw\/XZWdme0J70I\/AAAAAAAAenw\/H_OuG4ubDZAStcXQfErfSMvZrn8OKOXOwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Jq6JIpvh8DcVEkrx.png","title":"Berry Mousse","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"30 g","calories":"1184 kJ \/ 283 kcal"},"usefulItems":"dessert bowls, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Serve fruit mousse with a Berry Coulis.","Ricotta cheese can also be replaced with Cloumage, Quark or cream c